==Icelandic==
===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|[ˈd̥øyːðʏr]}}

===Adjective===
'''dauður'''

# [[dead]]

====Synonyms====
[[dáinn]] (past participle of [[deyja]] (to [[die]]))

====Usage note====
''dauður'' can sound heartless in modern Icelandic when used for someone the speaker, or the people they are speaking to, knew. Unless you are talking about a historical figure long gone or someone you didn't care about, use [[dáinn]] instead.

